    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">Does Happy Roof handle permits in Palm Harbor?<svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes. Palm Harbor is unincorporated Pinellas County, so permits go through the county building department. We handle all applications and inspections — you never need to visit a government office.</div></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">How long does a roof replacement take in Palm Harbor?<svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Most Palm Harbor shingle roofs are completed in 1 to 3 days. Metal roofs take 3 to 5 days, and tile roofs 5 to 7 days. We schedule around weather and provide updates throughout the project. Complete cleanup is always included.</div></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">Is Happy Roof licensed to work in Palm Harbor?<svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes. Happy Roof LLC holds Florida Roofing Contractor License #CCC1337380, authorizing roofing work throughout Florida including Palm Harbor and all of Pinellas County. We carry full general liability and workers' compensation insurance.</div></div></div>
